{"id":"sovereignty","term":"Sovereignty","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Of God, his absolute right to do all things according to his own good pleasure (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 4:25\">Dan. 4:25</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 4:35\">35</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 9:15\">Rom. 9:15-23</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 6:15\">1 Tim. 6:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 4:11\">Rev. 4:11</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Daniel 4:25","Daniel 4:35","Romans 9:15","1 Timothy 6:15","Revelation 4:11"]}